post1: What a blast from the past it was last night!   50 years since we all left Morgan and went out into the big wide world.   It was amazing to see some of the old faces, some I barely recognised while with others we went straight back to third year French class!  Awesome to catch up with Brucie, Govie and Tich, but sobering to hear about those who are no longer with us.   Be grateful for every day.
post2: Woo hoo!  Bill is 70!   How did I come to be married to such an old man???   Thank you for putting up with me for all these years and am looking forward to celebrating with you tonight.  Play your cards right - I might just have a wee surprise for you later on!  In the meantime enjoy your cake, it's your favourite!

post2: Congrats Jamie for surviving another year! It's definitely been a wild one between miving in, new job and adopting our first fur baby. Can't wait to make more memories like this with you.

post1: Tonight I discovered that if you hang out with a bunch of people who you were friends with in school but haven't seen for approximately.... 30 mumble years...., you will spend a LOT of the time feeling just as awkward as you did when you were a teenager, a LOT of the time comparing your current need for reading glasses and/or perimenopausal symptoms, and a LOT of the time feeling as though you've blocked out half your memories.
post2: 40 today! Happy birthday to S. At what point do you think people will stop saying "but you look about 12"? ?? Have a great day and I'll see you later for the birthday surprise. post2: To my lovely and supportive partner, whose birthday it is today, I hope you have a lovely need and get everything you wish for, you certainly deserve it, you have been a wonderful partner to me and such a good father to our sons, where would we be without you, you always put us first and show us you care, it means the world to us to know we have your love and support.
